        </figure>
        <para>
            <emph type="boldundersc">TESTING:</emph>
        </para>
        <seqlist style="arabic">
            <item>
                <para>Make proper trailer connections.</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Turn key on.</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Verify that the Orange wire marked R72EB has battery voltage.</para>
            </item>
        </seqlist>
        <para>
            <emph type="boldundersc">HOW DO I ADD THIS FEATURE:</emph>
        </para>
        <para>If the vehicle is not equipped with the fuse block shown below, one can be ordered from the dealer.</para>
        <para>The TEM will have to fabricate a 6-gauge jumper to go from the mega fuse to the maxi fuse block. The maxi
            fuse block requires a &#188; " eyelet and the mega fuse requires a 5/16" eyelet.
        </para>
        <figure id="f7300092a" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg73/G7300092.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="288px"
                     scalefitheight="272px"/>
            <caption></caption>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Identify the fuse function on the chart on the bottom of the PDC lid.</para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Locate a vacant ISO relay location in Power Distribution Center, under hood.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Supply
                <emph type="bold">Ignition</emph>
                power to Pin-5 of relay location.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Supply Ground to Pin-2 of relay location.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Supply fused (30 amp) battery power to Pin-1 of relay location.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Connect 10 gauge wire to Pin-4 of relay location.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Route 10 gauge wire with dash harness to center chassis harness. Continue to route wire with
                chassis harness to end of frame.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install relay and fuse.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Verify that wire at end of frame has battery voltage with key on, and is open with the key
                off.
            </para>
        </step1>
